<TITLE> DB get 4 more days to grill Zakir </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdbews24.com)  The Detective Branch of Police on Monday have four more days to grill Zakir Hossain alias Kailya Zakir in the case over the killing of sub inspector Gautam Kumar Roy. Dhaka's Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Nazrul Islam granted the time following their plea for seven days in an arms case filed on Monday, general recording officer of the court police, sub- inspector Shakhawat Hossain told bdnews24.com. Investigation officer (IO) of the case and DB sub-inspector Ruhul Amin presented Kailya Zakir before the court after 14 days' remand in the murder case. Gautam, based at Bangshal Police Station, was shot dead at Dholaikhal on Apr 20 midnight while coming back home after duty. RAB arrested Kailya Zakir, 25, on Apr 25. The IO said police and RAB have arrested six people so far in the murder case, where there is another 'Zakir'. The arms case was filed with Sutrapur Police Station on Monday. DB sub-inspector Gias Uddin has been put on the case. GRO Shakhawat said the police in their remand request stated that with the information provided by Kailya Zakir, a foreign pistol was recovered from a pile of waste at Brojohori Saha Street of Sutrapur. "He owns the pistol and it might be used in Gautam killing." Police suspect that Kailya Zakir has more arms in his possession. The remand request also said that police needed to take the men into custody to recover all the arms, including those used in the murder, and to detain his associates. bdn
